tents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_cc167fb6c80d5bd2d836d60510756195" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_27dd04d901334224abd5499a3e40eb32" parent="aspace_cc167fb6c80d5bd2d836d60510756195" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_4b6face5d64e706a34578c45f89e7ebf" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_59d07170d439ab4a5ed9ba1d2b4c2f31" parent="aspace_4b6face5d64e706a34578c45f89e7ebf" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_3a151c96e4525e4a8ff474297bb1fedf" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="a